{
  "stem": "1677.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 273.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he had a fiacre with his own couture, because he couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fiacre is in Vienna, is a [NON-ENGLISH], I don't know how you call it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's a carriage, a fiacre-- that's very typical, big wheels.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With one horse.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was Bartol.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And with that, he went to the post office.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he started WZO-- he was a great Zionist.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father had no religion, but he was a Zionist.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He spoke Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was at the second Zionist conference in Basel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was born in 1888, and he came important to this Hungarian-speaking Jewish community, who did not know where God lives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was a general manager, very high position, to this asbestos factory, started his chamber music, continued which he did in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And was probably bored stiff.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he met my mother, 16 years younger than him, and-- Helena.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Very spoiled, Budapest-educated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Very rich.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She had all the money, which I found out during the years, and he had a war pension, and he entered the business of my grandfather as a bookkeeper.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My grandfather didn't like him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember that because my grandfather was used to chalk up that people owed him on the counter or under the counter or give it to them on credit and not ask for their money back.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was loved and cherished by the peasants like a saint.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Normal people, when I say middle-class people, didn't come near him because he was a foul-mouthed old Slovak Jew, who had bacon for breakfast.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But on Yom Kippur he was in slippers all day long in the synagogue, and came home in the evening.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And with my father, they uttered the only sentence of the year, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they had a slivovitz, and the proceedings then went on.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
